article.description: Drakeford, CCSU top LIU Brooklyn 86-82 in OT
article.headline: Drakeford, CCSU top LIU Brooklyn 86-82 in OT
article.linkText: Drakeford, CCSU top LIU Brooklyn 86-82 in OT
article.story: NEW YORK -- Faronte Drakeford scored 25 points and Central Connecticut State went 7 of 7 from the free throw line in overtime as the Blue Devils beat LIU Brooklyn 86-82 Thursday night, securing a spot in the Northeast Conference tournament. Brandon Peel finished with a career-high 18 points and pulled down eight rebounds for CCSU (10-18, 6-9 Northeast Conference). E.J. Reed's layup with 1:01 left in overtime gave LIU Brooklyn (9-19, 4-11) an 80-79 lead but Drakeford completed a three-point play 32 seconds later and the Blue Devils never trailed again. Malcolm McMillan and Matt Mobley each made a pair of free throws in the final 11 seconds to seal the win. Kyle Vinales hit a deep 3-pointer as time expired in regulation to send the game into overtime. LIU Brooklyn's Gerrell Martin scored a career-high 31 points and Brickman finished with 12 points and 10 assists.
